  "prompt": "What is the platform in which Facebook is built?",
  "response": "Facebook is primarily built using various technologies and programming languages. Here are some key details:\n\n1. Backend\n- PHP (originally with the HipHop Virtual Machine, later converted to HHVM)\n- Hack programming language (a dialect of PHP developed by Facebook)\n- C++ for performance-critical components\n\n2. Frontend\n- JavaScript\n- React (a JavaScript library developed by Facebook)\n- React Native for mobile applications\n\n3. Infrastructure\n- Linux operating systems\n- MySQL and Cassandra for databases\n- Apache Hadoop for big data processing\n- Memcached and Redis for caching\n- GraphQL for API queries\n\n4. Mobile Platforms\n- React Native for cross-platform mobile development\n- Native iOS (Swift/Objective-C)\n- Native Android (Java/Kotlin)\n\nThe specific technologies have evolved over time, but these represent the core platforms and technologies used in Facebook's development.",
